xdsl_exo Architecture
=====================

xdsl_exo is a compiler that bridges Exo (a high-performance array DSL) with MLIR via xDSL.
It translates Exo procedures into MLIR, progressively lowers them through multiple dialects,
and emits LLVM-compatible IR with platform-specific vectorization (AVX2, BLAS).


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 DIRECTORY STRUCTURE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  xdsl_exo/
  │
  ├── __init__.py              public API: compile_one / compile_many / compile_path
  ├── __main__.py              CLI entry point
  ├── compiler.py              pipeline orchestration (analyze → generate → transform)
  ├── generator.py             Exo LoopIR AST  →  Exo MLIR dialect  (IRGenerator)
  │
  ├── dialects/                custom MLIR op definitions
  │   ├── exo.py               9 core ops (alloc, free, read, assign, reduce, window, ...)
  │   ├── index.py             index.casts op (Index ↔ integer)
  │   └── llvm_intrinsics.py   fabs, masked_store
  │
  ├── rewrites/                platform-independent lowering passes
  │   ├── inline_memory_space.py    propagate mem-space attrs through WindowOp
  │   ├── convert_scalar_ref.py     scalar args → memref<1xT>
  │   ├── convert_tensor_ref.py     exo dialect → memref dialect
  │   ├── convert_memref_to_llvm.py memref dialect → LLVM dialect
  │   ├── lower_alloc.py            exo.alloc → llvm.alloca  (stack)
  │   ├── add_prefix.py             rename func symbols with prefix
  │   └── reconcile_index_casts.py  remove redundant index.casts
  │
  └── platforms/               architecture-specific lowering passes
      ├── avx2.py              AVX2 intrinsics → LLVM vector ops  (4 converters)
      └── blas.py              BLAS + SIMD ops → LLVM             (75+ converters)


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 END-TO-END PIPELINE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │   Exo Python source file        │
  │   (@proc-decorated functions)   │
  └────────────────┬────────────────┘
                   │  compile_path() loads module,
                   │  extracts @proc objects
                   ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │   Exo Analysis (compiler.py)    │
  │   ├─ ParallelAnalysis           │
  │   ├─ PrecisionAnalysis          │
  │   ├─ WindowAnalysis             │
  │   └─ MemoryAnalysis             │
  └────────────────┬────────────────┘
                   │  annotated LoopIR AST
                   ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │   IRGenerator  (generator.py)   │
  │   Exo LoopIR → Exo MLIR dialect │
  │   produces: func.FuncOp wrapped │
  │   in a ModuleOp                 │
  └────────────────┬────────────────┘
                   │  ModuleOp  [Exo dialect]
                   ▼
  ╔═════════════════════════════════╗
  ║   transform()  (compiler.py)   ║
  ║   12-step lowering pipeline    ║
  ╚════════════════════════════════╝  (see PIPELINE section below)
                   │
                   │  ModuleOp  [LLVM dialect]
                   ▼
  ┌─────────────────────────────────┐
  │   Output MLIR                   │
  │   ready for mlir-opt / JIT /    │
  │   llc / assembly emission       │
  └─────────────────────────────────┘


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 TRANSFORMATION PIPELINE  (compiler.transform())
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  [Exo dialect]
       │
       │  1. InlineMemorySpacePass
       │     propagate "DRAM" / "VEC_AVX2" mem-space attrs through WindowOps
       │
       │  2. ConvertScalarRefPass
       │     mutated scalar args → memref<1xT>  (uniform representation)
       │
       │  3. ReconcileIndexCastsPass
       │     remove round-trip index.casts  (i64→index→i64 ⟹ i64)
       │
       │  4. CanonicalizePass + CSE
       │     standard cleanup and common subexpression elimination
       │
       │  5. AddPrefixPass  (optional, controlled by CompilerOptions.prefix)
       │     rename all func.FuncOp symbols with a user-supplied prefix
       │
       │  6. InlineBLASAllocPass
       │     lower BLAS-specific alloc/free (VEC_AVX2 memory space)
       │
  [exo + memref mixed]
       │
       │  7. ConvertMemRefToLLVM
       │     exo.read/assign/reduce/window → GEP + llvm.load/store
       │     exo.alloc → malloc,  exo.free → free
       │     all MemRefType → opaque LLVM pointer (!llvm.ptr)
       │
  [LLVM dialect, but still has platform intrinsics]
       │
       │  8. InlineAVX2Pass
       │     _mm256_loadu_ps / _storeu_ps / _fmadd_ps / _broadcast_ss
       │     → llvm vector load / store / fma ops
       │
       │  9. InlineBLASPass
       │     75+ SIMD op converters  (f32×8, f64×4, masked variants)
       │     → llvm arith, vector.fma, llvm.intr.fabs, masked_store
       │
       │  10. ConvertScfToCf
       │      scf.for / scf.if → cf.br / cf.cond_br  (branch-based CFG)
       │
       │  11. ReconcileUnrealizedCasts
       │      remove leftover unrealized_conversion_cast ops
       │
       │  12. CanonicalizePass + CSE
       │      final cleanup
       │
  [pure LLVM dialect]


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 DIALECT LAYERS  (IR representation at each stage)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Stage 0 – Exo LoopIR AST (Python objects, not MLIR)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Stmt: Assign | Reduce | For | If | Alloc | Free | Call | WindowStmt
  Expr: Read | Const | BinOp | USub | WindowExpr | Extern

  Stage 1 – Exo MLIR dialect  (after IRGenerator)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────
  exo.alloc   : () → memref<...xT>           mem = "DRAM" | "VEC_AVX2"
  exo.free    : (memref) → ()
  exo.read    : (memref, indices...) → T     with static_sizes attr
  exo.assign  : (memref, T, indices...) → () with static_sizes attr
  exo.reduce  : (memref, T, indices...) → () load + add + store
  exo.window  : (memref, intervals...) → memref<subview>
  exo.interval: (start, end) → tuple         [start, end) range
  exo.instr   : (args...) → (results...)     named intrinsic call
  exo.extern  : (args...) → T               external C call

  Stage 2 – memref dialect  (after ConvertTensorRefPass)
  ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  exo.read    → memref.load
  exo.assign  → memref.store
  exo.reduce  → memref.load + arith.addf + memref.store
  exo.window  → memref.subview  (strides/offsets computed from intervals)

  Stage 3 – LLVM dialect  (after ConvertMemRefToLLVM)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  All MemRefType            → !llvm.ptr  (opaque pointer)
  memref.load / store       → llvm.getelementptr + llvm.load / store
  exo.alloc                 → llvm.call @malloc
  exo.free                  → llvm.call @free
  exo.window                → llvm.getelementptr + llvm.bitcast


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 IRGENERATOR  (generator.py)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  IRGenerator
  ├── generate(procs)               → ModuleOp
  │     └── generate_procedure()   → func.FuncOp
  │           └── generate_stmt_list()
  │
  ├── generate_stmt(stmt)
  │   ├── Assign      → exo.AssignOp
  │   ├── Reduce      → exo.ReduceOp
  │   ├── For         → scf.ForOp  (+  YieldOp)
  │   ├── If          → scf.IfOp   (+  true/false blocks)
  │   ├── Alloc       → exo.AllocOp
  │   ├── Free        → exo.FreeOp
  │   ├── Call        → func.CallOp  or  exo.InstrOp
  │   └── WindowStmt  → exo.WindowOp
  │
  ├── generate_expr(expr)
  │   ├── Read        → exo.ReadOp  (memref)  or  direct SSAValue (scalar)
  │   ├── Const       → arith.ConstantOp
  │   ├── BinOp       → arith.{Addf,Addi,Mulf,Muli,Cmpf,Cmpi,...}
  │   ├── USub        → arith.NegfOp  or  arith.SubiOp (from zero)
  │   ├── WindowExpr  → exo.WindowOp  +  exo.IntervalOp
  │   └── Extern      → exo.ExternOp
  │
  └── state
      ├── symbol_table : ScopedDict[Sym → SSAValue]   (current SSA values)
      └── type_table   : ScopedDict[Sym → ExoType]    (for shape/type queries)

  Type mapping:
    T.F16  → f16       T.F32  → f32       T.F64  → f64
    T.I8   → i8        T.I16  → i16       T.I32  → i32    T.I64  → i64
    Tensor[shape, T]   → memref<d0×d1×...×T>
    Tensor[?, T]       → memref<?×T>  (dynamic dim)
    scalar (mutated)   → memref<1×T>  (after ConvertScalarRefPass)


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 PLATFORM PASSES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  platforms/avx2.py  —  InlineAVX2Pass
  ─────────────────────────────────────
  exo.InstrOp callee              →  LLVM ops
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  _mm256_loadu_ps   (ptr)         →  llvm.load  vector<8xf32>
  _mm256_storeu_ps  (ptr, vec)    →  llvm.store vector<8xf32>
  _mm256_fmadd_ps   (a, b, c)     →  load a, b, c → vector.fma → store
  _mm256_broadcast_ss (scalar)    →  vector.broadcast → llvm.store


  platforms/blas.py  —  InlineBLASPass  (75+ converters)
  ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Operation family    Widths         Variants
  ──────────────────  ─────────────  ──────────────────────────────
  alloc / free        VEC_AVX2       stack via llvm.alloca
  abs                 f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed (masked)
  add                 f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed, reduce, copy
  load / store        f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed
  multiply            f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed, negate
  fma (1 acc)         f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed, reduce
  fma (2 acc)         f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed, reduce
  zero                f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed
  broadcast scalar    f32×8, f64×4   plain, prefixed

  "plain"    = full-width vector operation
  "prefixed" = masked variant for partial vectors (edge iterations)


━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
 KEY DESIGN PATTERNS
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Progressive lowering
  ────────────────────
  Each pass handles exactly one layer transition.
  No pass skips levels. IR is always in a well-defined dialect.

  ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐     ┌──────────────┐
  │ Exo dialect  │ ──► │    memref    │ ──► │     LLVM     │
  │  (semantic)  │     │  (abstract   │     │  (concrete   │
  │              │     │   memory)    │     │   machine)   │
  └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘     └──────────────┘

  Pattern rewriting
  ─────────────────
  Every pass is implemented as a set of RewritePattern subclasses
  applied via GreedyRewritePatternApplier.

  class ConvertReadOp(RewritePattern):
      @op_type_rewrite_pattern
      def match_and_rewrite(self, op: ReadOp, rewriter: PatternRewriter):
          ...  # replace op with lower-level ops

  Scoped symbol tables
  ────────────────────
  IRGenerator maintains two ScopedDict instances that mirror
  the nesting of Exo scopes (function → loop → if-branch):

  outer scope  { x → SSAValue, y → SSAValue }
     inner scope (loop body) { i → SSAValue, ... }
        inner scope (if-true) { ... }

  Memory space as metadata
  ────────────────────────
  Memory spaces travel as StringAttr properties on AllocOp/FreeOp.
  They are invisible to generic passes and consumed only by
  platform-specific passes that understand them.

  exo.alloc {mem = "VEC_AVX2"} : memref<8xf32>
       │
       │  passes 1–5 ignore the attr
       │
       ▼
  InlineBLASAllocPass sees "VEC_AVX2" → emits llvm.alloca with alignment

  Dynamic shape handling
  ──────────────────────
  Static dims  → DenseArrayBase property  (compile-time constant)
  Dynamic dims → var_operand_def operands (SSA values at runtime)
  split_dynamic_index_list() zips them back together for GEP emission.
